  <a href="#1" id="1">
   East Germany's ousted Secret Police Chief Erich Mielke,
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   when he faced former Communist leader Erich Honecker,
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   called him a traitor and threatened to break his neck.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Honecker was jailed in January
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   but was released after one day for health reasons.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   Mielke, one of Honecker's closest aides, headed the dreaded secret police know as Stasi.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   One prison warden said
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   that many of the guards had worked for Mielke's Stasi
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   and might interpret his threat as an order to kill Honecker,
  </a>
  <a href="#10" id="10">
   who will be moved to the same jail
  </a>
  <a href="#11" id="11">
   if his health improves.
  </a>
  <a href="#12" id="12">
   He is in a hospital and suffering from kidney cancer.
  </a>
